						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Vishṇumūrti temple.</p>						

						<p>Vīra-Pāṇḍyadēva, 1267 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record is dated the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Prabhava, Siṁha,</hi> in the reign of Vīra-Pāṇḍyadēva Āḷpēndra and so might be assigned to <hi rend="bold">1267 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It refers to an <hi rend="italic">aḍaka-patra</hi> issued in the presence of the <hi rend="italic">pradhānas</hi> and other officials of the palace at <hi rend="bold">Bārakanyāpura,</hi> registering a gift of the village Puttige and stipulating payment of taxes like <hi rend="italic">samudāya</hi> to the king.</p>						

						</summary>
